1 Introduction

The data that we are going to use for this exercise is published in the mBio paper (Niggli S 2023). It can be found online on: https://doi.org/10.6084/m9.figshare.23578086.v1 It describes the OD600 (growth) of the Staphylococcus aureus strain JE2 in different media.

2 Reading in Data and Plotting Growth Curves

fN <- "JE_growth_final.txt" # us this txt file that is copy pasted spread sheet from excel tab separated 
dat <- read.table(fN, header = T, sep = "\t", stringsAsFactors = TRUE)
## [1] 8220    6

The dimensions of this dataset are shown above. It is easy possible to show also content of variables in the html part.
Note: if you end a line with 2 spaces you go to a new paragraph.

Like here: 8220, 6

library(ggplot2)
ggplot(dat, aes(x = Time, y = OD600_blank_corrected, color = Growth_Medium)) + geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(method = "loess", size = 1.2) + 
  labs(title = "Growth Curves (Smoothed Regression)",
       x = "Time (hours)",
       y = "OD600 (Blank Corrected)",
       color = "Growth Medium") +
  theme_minimal()
